summary: This is an email chain from January 28, 2020, discussing United Airlines flight records. The correspondence indicates there were only two flight records found: one for an unspecified individual in January 2020 and one for another unspecified individual booked by the DOJ in August 2019. No records were found for Ghislaine Maxwell. The emails show prosecutors struggling to interpret the records and considering calling a custodian witness to explain them to a grand jury.

events.title: Flight Record Search for Unnamed Individual
events.description: United Airlines records show one flight for an unspecified individual in January 2020.

events.title: DOJ-Booked Flight for Unnamed Individual
events.description: United Airlines records show one flight for an unspecified individual that was booked by the Department of Justice in August 2019.

keyFacts: United Airlines flight records were obtained and reviewed by prosecutors in January 2020.
The records showed only two relevant flights: one in January 2020 for an unnamed individual, and one booked by the DOJ in August 2019 for another unnamed individual.
No flight records were found for Ghislaine Maxwell in the provided data.
Prosecutors found the records difficult to interpret and considered calling a custodian witness to explain them to a grand jury.
The email chain demonstrates investigative efforts to trace travel patterns, with the DOJ itself having booked a flight for an individual in August 2019.
